title: Spanish PM axes Catalan government after region declares independence
description:
Catalan lawmakers declared independence from Spain Friday after a controversial and widely disputed vote in favour of secession. Hours later, Spanish Prime Minister Mariano Rajoy labelled the vote "criminal," fired Catalonia's political leaders and dissolved its regional parliament. 

Welcome to The National, the flagship nightly newscast of CBC News
